The paper deals with the computation of Abelian periods of a word, which is a problem related to string algorithms and combinatorics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the use of logarithmic time algorithms, which suggests the category cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Additionally, the paper involves the use of complexity analysis, which suggests the category cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves the use of information theory concepts, which suggests the category cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves experimental results, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
